</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML MJX_Assistive_MathML_Block" role="presentation">(1.1.2)limx&rarr;3x2&minus;x&minus;66x2&minus;19x+3.</span></span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="lt-math-4150"><strong>Solution:</strong><br>To graphically approximate the limit, graph</p>\r\n<p class="lt-math-4150">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class="MathJax_Display"><span id="MathJax-Element-102-Frame" class="MathJax MathJax_FullWidth" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: center; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; width: 10000em !important; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot; display=&quot;block&quot;&gt;&lt;mtable displaystyle=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;mlabeledtr&gt;&lt;mtd id=&quot;mjx-eqn-1.1.3&quot;&gt;&lt;mtext&gt;(1.1.3)&lt;/mtext&gt;&lt;/mtd&gt;&lt;mtd&gt;&lt;mi&gt;y&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;2&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&amp;#x2212;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&amp;#x2212;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;6&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mrow class=&quot;MJX-TeXAtom-ORD&quot;&gt;&lt;mo&gt;/&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;6&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;2&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&amp;#x2212;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;19&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;3&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mtd&gt;&lt;/mlabeledtr&gt;&lt;/mtable&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-573" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-574" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-575" class="mtable"><span id="MathJax-Span-579" class="mtd"><span id="MathJax-Span-580" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-581" class="mi">y</span><span id="MathJax-Span-582" class="mo">=</span><span id="MathJax-Span-583" class="mo">(</span><span id="MathJax-Span-584" class="msubsup"><span id="MathJax-Span-585" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-586" class="mn">2</span></span><span id="MathJax-Span-587" class="mo">&minus;</span><span id="MathJax-Span-588" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-589" class="mo">&minus;</span><span id="MathJax-Span-590" class="mn">6</span><span id="MathJax-Span-591" class="mo">)</span><span id="MathJax-Span-592" class="texatom"><span id="MathJax-Span-593" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-594" class="mo">/</span></span></span><span id="MathJax-Span-595" class="mo">(</span><span id="MathJax-Span-596" class="mn">6</span><span id="MathJax-Span-597" class="msubsup"><span id="MathJax-Span-598" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-599" class="mn">2</span></span><span id="MathJax-Span-600" class="mo">&minus;</span><span id="MathJax-Span-601" class="mn">19</span><span id="MathJax-Span-602" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-603" class="mo">+</span><span id="MathJax-Span-604" class="mn">3</span><span id="MathJax-Span-605" class="mo">)</span></span></span><span id="mjx-eqn-1.1.3" class="mtd"><span id="MathJax-Span-577" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-578" class="mtext">(1.1.3)</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML MJX_Assistive_MathML_Block" role="presentation">(1.1.3)y=(x2&minus;x&minus;6)/(6x2&minus;19x+3)</span></span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="lt-math-4150">on a small interval that contains 3. To numerically approximate the limit, create a table of values where the&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-103-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-606" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-607" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-608" class="mi">x</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">x</span></span>&nbsp;values are near 3. This is done in Figures 1.5 and 1.6, respectively.</p>\r\n<p class="lt-math-4150">The graph shows that when&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-104-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-609" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-610" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-611" class="mi">x</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">x</span></span>&nbsp;is near 3, the value of&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-105-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;y&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-612" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-613" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-614" class="mi">y</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">y</span></span>&nbsp;is very near&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-106-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0.3&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-615" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-616" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-617" class="mn">0.3</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">0.3</span></span>. By considering values of&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-107-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-618" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-619" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-620" class="mi">x</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">x</span></span>&nbsp;near 3, we see that&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-108-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;y&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0.294&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-621" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-622" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-623" class="mi">y</span><span id="MathJax-Span-624" class="mo">=</span><span id="MathJax-Span-625" class="mn">0.294</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">y=0.294</span></span>&nbsp;is a better approximation. The graph and the table imply that</p>\r\n<p class="lt-math-4150">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class="MathJax_Display"><span id="MathJax-Element-109-Frame" class="MathJax MathJax_FullWidth" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: center; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; width: 10000em !important; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot; display=&quot;block&quot;&gt;&lt;mtable displaystyle=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;mlabeledtr&gt;&lt;mtd id=&quot;mjx-eqn-1.1.4&quot;&gt;&lt;mtext&gt;(1.1.4)&lt;/mtext&gt;&lt;/mtd&gt;&lt;mtd&gt;&lt;munder&gt;&lt;mo movablelimits=&quot;true&quot; form=&quot;prefix&quot;&gt;lim&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mrow class=&quot;MJX-TeXAtom-ORD&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;&amp;#x2192;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;3&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/munder&gt;&lt;mfrac&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;2&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&amp;#x2212;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&amp;#x2212;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;6&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mn&gt;6&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;2&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&amp;#x2212;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;19&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;3&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mfrac&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&amp;#x2248;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0.294.&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mtd&gt;&lt;/mlabeledtr&gt;&lt;/mtable&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-626" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-627" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-628" class="mtable"><span id="MathJax-Span-632" class="mtd"><span id="MathJax-Span-633" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-634" class="munderover"><span id="MathJax-Span-635" class="mo">lim</span><span id="MathJax-Span-636" class="texatom"><span id="MathJax-Span-637" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-638" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-639" class="mo">&rarr;</span><span id="MathJax-Span-640" class="mn">3</span></span></span></span><span id="MathJax-Span-641" class="mfrac"><span id="MathJax-Span-642" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-643" class="msubsup"><span id="MathJax-Span-644" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-645" class="mn">2</span></span><span id="MathJax-Span-646" class="mo">&minus;</span><span id="MathJax-Span-647" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-648" class="mo">&minus;</span><span id="MathJax-Span-649" class="mn">6</span></span><span id="MathJax-Span-650" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-651" class="mn">6</span><span id="MathJax-Span-652" class="msubsup"><span id="MathJax-Span-653" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-654" class="mn">2</span></span><span id="MathJax-Span-655" class="mo">&minus;</span><span id="MathJax-Span-656" class="mn">19</span><span id="MathJax-Span-657" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-658" class="mo">+</span><span id="MathJax-Span-659" class="mn">3</span></span></span><span id="MathJax-Span-660" class="mo">&asymp;</span><span id="MathJax-Span-661" class="mn">0.294.</span></span></span><span id="mjx-eqn-1.1.4" class="mtd"><span id="MathJax-Span-630" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-631" class="mtext">(1.1.4)</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML MJX_Assistive_MathML_Block" role="presentation">(1.1.4)limx&rarr;3x2&minus;x&minus;66x2&minus;19x+3&asymp;0.294.</span></span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p class="lt-math-4150">This example may bring up a few questions about approximating limits (and the nature of limits themselves).</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li class="lt-math-4150">If a graph does not produce as good an approximation as a table, why bother with it?</li>\r\n<li class="lt-math-4150">How many values of&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-110-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-662" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-663" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-664" class="mi">x</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">x</span></span>&nbsp;in a table are "enough?\'\' In the previous example, could we have just used&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-111-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;3.001&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-665" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-666" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-667" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-668" class="mo">=</span><span id="MathJax-Span-669" class="mn">3.001</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">x=3.001</span></span>&nbsp;and found a fine approximation?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p class="lt-math-4150">Graphs are useful since they give a visual understanding concerning the behavior of a function. Sometimes a function may act "erratically\'\' near certain&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-112-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-670" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-671" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-672" class="mi">x</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">x</span></span>&nbsp;values which is hard to discern numerically but very plain graphically. Since graphing utilities are very accessible, it makes sense to make proper use of them.</p>\r\n<p class="lt-math-4150">Since tables and graphs are used only to&nbsp;<em>approximate</em>&nbsp;the value of a limit, there is not a firm answer to how many data points are "enough.\'\' Include enough so that a trend is clear, and use values (when possible) both less than and greater than the value in question. In Example 1, we used both values less than and greater than 3. Had we used just&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-113-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;3.001&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-673" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-674" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-675" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-676" class="mo">=</span><span id="MathJax-Span-677" class="mn">3.001</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">x=3.001</span></span>, we might have been tempted to conclude that the limit had a value of&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-114-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0.3&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-678" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-679" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-680" class="mn">0.3</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">0.3</span></span>. While this is not far off, we could do better. Using values "on both sides of 3\'\' helps us identify trends.</p>\r\n<div class="box-example">\r\n<p class="box-legend lt-math-4150">Example 2: Approximating the value of a limit</p>\r\n<p class="lt-math-4150">Graphically and numerically approximate the limit of&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-115-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-681" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-682" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-683" class="mi">f</span><span id="MathJax-Span-684" class="mo">(</span><span id="MathJax-Span-685" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-686" class="mo">)</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">f(x)</span></span>&nbsp;as&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-116-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-687" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-688" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-689" class="mi">x</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">x</span></span>&nbsp;approaches 0, where</p>\r\n<p class="lt-math-4150">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class="MathJax_Display"><span id="MathJax-Element-117-Frame" class="MathJax MathJax_FullWidth" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: center; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; width: 10000em !important; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot; display=&quot;block&quot;&gt;&lt;mtable displaystyle=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;mlabeledtr&gt;&lt;mtd id=&quot;mjx-eqn-1.1.5&quot;&gt;&lt;mtext&gt;(1.1.5)&lt;/mtext&gt;&lt;/mtd&gt;&lt;mtd&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mo&gt;{&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mtable columnalign=&quot;right left&quot; rowspacing=&quot;4pt&quot; columnspacing=&quot;1em&quot;&gt;&lt;mtr&gt;&lt;mtd&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mtd&gt;&lt;mtd&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mtd&gt;&lt;/mtr&gt;&lt;mtr&gt;&lt;mtd&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&amp;#x2212;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;2&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mtd&gt;&lt;mtd&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mtd&gt;&lt;/mtr&gt;&lt;/mtable&gt;&lt;mo fence=&quot;true&quot; stretchy=&quot;true&quot; symmetric=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mtd&gt;&lt;/mlabeledtr&gt;&lt;/mtable&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-690" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-691" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-692" class="mtable"><span id="MathJax-Span-696" class="mtd"><span id="MathJax-Span-697" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-698" class="mi">f</span><span id="MathJax-Span-699" class="mo">(</span><span id="MathJax-Span-700" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-701" class="mo">)</span><span id="MathJax-Span-702" class="mo">=</span><span id="MathJax-Span-703" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-704" class="mo">{</span><span id="MathJax-Span-705" class="mtable"><span id="MathJax-Span-706" class="mtd"><span id="MathJax-Span-707" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-708" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-709" class="mo">+</span><span id="MathJax-Span-710" class="mn">1</span></span></span><span id="MathJax-Span-716" class="mtd"><span id="MathJax-Span-717" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-718" class="mo">&minus;</span><span id="MathJax-Span-719" class="msubsup"><span id="MathJax-Span-720" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-721" class="mn">2</span></span><span id="MathJax-Span-722" class="mo">+</span><span id="MathJax-Span-723" class="mn">1</span></span></span><span id="MathJax-Span-711" class="mtd"><span id="MathJax-Span-712" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-713" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-714" class="mo">&lt;</span><span id="MathJax-Span-715" class="mn">0</span></span></span><span id="MathJax-Span-724" class="mtd"><span id="MathJax-Span-725" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-726" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-727" class="mo">&gt;</span><span id="MathJax-Span-728" class="mn">0</span></span></span></span><span id="MathJax-Span-729" class="mo"></span></span></span></span><span id="mjx-eqn-1.1.5" class="mtd"><span id="MathJax-Span-694" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-695" class="mtext">(1.1.5)</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML MJX_Assistive_MathML_Block" role="presentation">(1.1.5)f(x)={x+1x&lt;0&minus;x2+1x&gt;0</span></span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="lt-math-4150"><strong>Solution:</strong><br>Again we graph&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-118-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-730" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-731" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-732" class="mi">f</span><span id="MathJax-Span-733" class="mo">(</span><span id="MathJax-Span-734" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-735" class="mo">)</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">f(x)</span></span>&nbsp;and create a table of its values near&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-119-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-736" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-737" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-738" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-739" class="mo">=</span><span id="MathJax-Span-740" class="mn">0</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">x=0</span></span>&nbsp;to approximate the limit. Note that this is a piecewise defined function, so it behaves differently on either side of 0. Figure 1.7 shows a graph of&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-120-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-741" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-742" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-743" class="mi">f</span><span id="MathJax-Span-744" class="mo">(</span><span id="MathJax-Span-745" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-746" class="mo">)</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">f(x)</span></span>, and on either side of 0 it seems the&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-121-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;y&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-747" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-748" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-749" class="mi">y</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">y</span></span>&nbsp;values approach 1. Note that&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-122-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-750" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-751" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-752" class="mi">f</span><span id="MathJax-Span-753" class="mo">(</span><span id="MathJax-Span-754" class="mn">0</span><span id="MathJax-Span-755" class="mo">)</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">f(0)</span></span>&nbsp;is not actually defined, as indicated in the graph with the open circle.</p>\r\n<p class="mt-align-center lt-math-4150"><img class="internal" src="https://math.libretexts.org/@api/deki/files/3600/1.7.png?revision=1&amp;size=bestfit&amp;width=397&amp;height=391" alt="alt" width="397px" height="391px" loading="lazy"><br><span id="MathJax-Element-123-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mtext&gt;FIGURE 1.7&lt;/mtext&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-756" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-757" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-758" class="mtext">FIGURE 1.7</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">FIGURE 1.7</span></span>: Graphically approximating a limit in Example 2.</p>\r\n<p class="mt-align-center lt-math-4150"><img class="internal" src="https://math.libretexts.org/@api/deki/files/3601/1.8.png?revision=1&amp;size=bestfit&amp;width=198&amp;height=200" alt="alt" width="198px" height="200px" loading="lazy"><br><span id="MathJax-Element-124-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mtext&gt;FIGURE 1.8&lt;/mtext&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-759" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-760" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-761" class="mtext">FIGURE 1.8</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">FIGURE 1.8</span></span>: Numerically approximating a limit in Example 2.</p>\r\n<p class="lt-math-4150">The table shown in Figure 1.8 shows values of&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-125-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-762" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-763" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-764" class="mi">f</span><span id="MathJax-Span-765" class="mo">(</span><span id="MathJax-Span-766" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-767" class="mo">)</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">f(x)</span></span>&nbsp;for values of&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-126-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-768" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-769" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-770" class="mi">x</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">x</span></span>&nbsp;near 0. It is clear that as&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-127-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-771" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-772" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-773" class="mi">x</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">x</span></span>&nbsp;takes on values very near 0,&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-128-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-774" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-775" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-776" class="mi">f</span><span id="MathJax-Span-777" class="mo">(</span><span id="MathJax-Span-778" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-779" class="mo">)</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">f(x)</span></span>&nbsp;takes on values very near 1. It turns out that if we let&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-129-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-780" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-781" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-782" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-783" class="mo">=</span><span id="MathJax-Span-784" class="mn">0</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">x=0</span></span>&nbsp;for either "piece\'\' of&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-130-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-785" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-786" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-787" class="mi">f</span><span id="MathJax-Span-788" class="mo">(</span><span id="MathJax-Span-789" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-790" class="mo">)</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">f(x)</span></span>, 1 is returned; this is significant and we\'ll return to this idea later.</p>\r\n<p class="lt-math-4150">The graph and table allow us to say that&nbsp;<span id="MathJax-Element-131-Frame" class="MathJax" style="display: inline-table; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-size: 17.6px; text-indent: 0px; text-align: left; text-transform: none; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; white-space: nowrap; float: none; direction: ltr; max-width: none; max-height: none; min-width: 0px; min-height: 0px; border: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; position: relative;" tabindex="0" role="presentation" data-mathml="&lt;math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;&gt;&lt;munder&gt;&lt;mo movablelimits=&quot;true&quot; form=&quot;prefix&quot;&gt;lim&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mrow class=&quot;MJX-TeXAtom-ORD&quot;&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;&amp;#x2192;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/munder&gt;&lt;mi&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;&amp;#x2248;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/math&gt;"><span id="MathJax-Span-791" class="math"><span id="MathJax-Span-792" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-793" class="munderover"><span id="MathJax-Span-794" class="mo">lim</span><span id="MathJax-Span-795" class="texatom"><span id="MathJax-Span-796" class="mrow"><span id="MathJax-Span-797" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-798" class="mo">&rarr;</span><span id="MathJax-Span-799" class="mn">0</span></span></span></span><span id="MathJax-Span-800" class="mi">f</span><span id="MathJax-Span-801" class="mo">(</span><span id="MathJax-Span-802" class="mi">x</span><span id="MathJax-Span-803" class="mo">)</span><span id="MathJax-Span-804" class="mo">&asymp;</span><span id="MathJax-Span-805" class="mn">1</span></span></span><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation">limx&rarr;0f(x)&asymp;1</span></span>; in fact, we are probably very sure it&nbsp;<em>equals</em>&nbsp;1.</p>\r\n</div>', '/Uploads/topic-53412-understanding-limit-notation.png', '23fdb2ea-cc30-11ec-a798-00d861bb616d'),
